\pard\f0\fs28\qc  {\b 14.        Chamorchis}     L.C.M. Richard
\par

\pard\f0\fs24\qc  By D.A. Webb. 
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28 Tubers 2, ellipsoid. Leaves all basal; stem without scale-leaves. Perianth-segments connivent into a galea, the three outer equal, somewhat longer than the inner. Labellum slightly longer than the other perianth-segments, ovate, entire or shallowly 3-lobed. Spur absent. Rostellum inconspicuous. Viscidia distinct; bursicle simple.
\par

