\pard\f0\fs28 Tubers laterally compressed, palmately lobed. Stem leafy. Flowers in a spike. Outer lateral perianth-segments patent or curved downwards, the outer median connivent with the inner lateral to form a galea. Labellum shallowly 3-lobed, directed downwards. Spur long, slender. Column short,erect. Rostellum long. Viscidia 2, long, linear; bursicles absent.
