\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. P. albida} (L.) Á. & D. Löve,{\i  Taxon}{\b  18}: 312 (1969). ({\i Leucorchis albida} (L.) E. H. F. Meyer, {\i Gymnadenia albida} (L.) L. C. M. Richard). Tubers divided to base, with the slender cylindrical divisions thickened distally. Stem 12-30(-40) cm, erect, glabrous, with 2-3 membranous sheathing scales at base. Lower leaves c. 4, 2·5-8 × 1-1·5 cm, obtuse; upper leaves 1-2, narrower, acute. Spike 3-7 cm, cylindrical, dense, many-flowered; bracts 3-veined. Flowers 2-3 mm, yellowish- or greenish-white. Outer perianth-segments obtuse, the lateral obliquely ovate, the median ovate, concave; inner slightly shorter, oblong-ovate, obtuse. Labellum 3-lobed; lateral lobes linear-lanceolate, acuminate; middle lobe larger, rather obtuse. Spur 2(-2·5) mm, 1/3-1/2 as long as ovary, cylindrical, obtuse, thickened distally and somewhat curved downwards.{\i  Damp meadows, pastures and grassy heaths. Europe, southwards to the Pyrenees, S. Appennini and S. Bulgaria, but absent from the U.S.S.R. except the extreme north and west}. Au Be Br Bu Cz Da Fa Fe Ga Ge Hb He †Ho Hs Is It Ju No Po Rm Rs (N, W) Su.
\par

\par

\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b a}) Subsp. {\b albida}: Lower leaves usually oblong-spathulate, erect. Spike very dense; bracts equalling ovary, with minutely denticulate margin. Lateral outer perianth-segments 2-3 mm. •{\i  Throughout most of the range of the species, northwards to C. Sweden}.
\par

\pard\f0\fs28   ({\b b}) Subsp. {\b straminea} (Fernald) Á. & D. Löve, {\i loc. cit.} (1969) ({\i Leucorchis albida} subsp. {\i straminea }(Fernald) Á. Löve): Lower leaves usually ovate-oblong, more or less patent. Spike often shorter and less dense than in subsp. ({\b a}). Bracts exceeding ovary, with entire or minutely crenulate margin. Lateral outer perianth-segments more than 3 mm. 2n = 40, 42.{\i  N. Europe, southwards to S. Norway}.
